e = \"DroneManager\"\n\tadd_child(_drone_manager)\n\t_drone_manager.setup(Vector3.ZERO)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: drone manager ready\")\n\nfunc _setup_travel_sequence() -> void:\n\t_travel_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n\t_travel_manager.name = \"TravelSequenceManager\"\n\tadd_child(_travel_manager)\n\t_travel_manager.setup(_player, _ship_exterior, _biome_content)\n\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_started.connect(_on_travel_sequence_started)\n\t_travel_manager.travel_sequence_completed.connect(_on_travel_sequence_completed)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence manager ready\")\n\nfunc _on_travel_sequence_started(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\t_transitioning = true\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\nfunc _on_travel_sequence_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\t_transitioning = false\n\t# ShipEnterZone is a child of _ship_exterior, so it follows the ship automatically (TICKET-0207).\n\t# No manual repositioning needed here.\n\t# Update ship interior exterior marker to match new ship position\n\tif _ship_interior and _ship_exterior:\n\t\tvar exit_offset: Vector3 = Vector3(0.0, 0.0, 24.0)\n\t\t_ship_interior.set_exterior_position(_ship_exterior.position + exit_offset)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TestWorld: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)","numLines":30,"startLine":540,"totalLines":649}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EsXEJdymcpcGcoQ4bsxybL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so at line 551, `add_child(_travel_manager)` is called BEFORE `_travel_manager.setup(...)` on line 552. That means the TravelSequenceManager IS in the tree when `setup()` is called. And `_build_fade_overlay()` checks `is_inside_tree()`, which should return true at that point.\n\nSo `_fade_rect` should be properly initialized. Let me verify once more:\n\n1. `add_child(_travel_manager)` — adds to tree\n2. `_travel_manager.setup(...)` — calls `_build_fade_overlay()`\n\n\n3. `_build_fade_overlay()` — `is_inside_tree()` returns true, so it builds `_fade_layer` and `_fade_rect`\n\nThe overlay should definitely exist then. Now I'm looking at `_fade_out()` to see what could be failing — it checks if `_fade_rect` exists and if the node is in the tree before creating the tween that animates the fade.\n\nThe tween itself should work since it's created on TravelSequenceManager which is in the tree, but I'm wondering if `_fade_rect` could have been freed or invalidated somehow. Let me trace back through the wave 2 reorder — the panel closes before `initiate_travel()` is called, which means `_close_for_travel()` starts a tween on the panel...\n\nStill writing tween logic... ends the await. Control flows back through `initiate_travel()`, which emits `biome_changed` and returns, then back to `_on_confirm_pressed()` which logs and exits. Meanwhile, both animations are running in parallel—the NavigationConsole closes after 0.15 seconds while the fade-out completes after 0.5 seconds, at which point the biome swap should occur. But I'm wondering if there's a `process_mode` issue at play here—if disabling gameplay inputs pauses the tree or changes how tweens process, that could throw off the timing.\n\nLet me check what InputManager is actually doing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":67575,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":929},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"426a97be-3db4-4386-86bc-19417547e39d"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EsXEJdymcpcGcoQ4bsxybL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FFwD5LaeNuercuNhPEoPnM","name":"Grep","i