d":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"4bcebd46-021e-4e1a-9e7f-edf4e4affd51","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\autoloads\\InputManager.gd","content":"\t\t\t_switch_input_device(\"gamepad\")\n\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\t_device_switch_timer += delta\n\n# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n## Enables or disables gameplay input processing.\n## When disabled, gameplay actions return false/zero; UI actions (ui_*) still work.\nfunc set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(enabled: bool) -> void:\n\t_gameplay_inputs_enabled = enabled\n\n## Returns true if gameplay inputs are currently enabled.\nfunc is_gameplay_inputs_enabled() -> bool:\n\treturn _gameplay_inputs_enabled\n\n## Returns true if the specified action is currently pressed.\nfunc is_action_pressed(action: String) -> bool:\n\tif not _gameplay_inputs_enabled and action in GAMEPLAY_ACTIONS:\n\t\treturn false\n\treturn Input.is_action_pressed(action)\n\n## Returns true if the specified action was just pressed this frame.\nfunc is_action_just_pressed(action: String) -> bool:\n\tif not _gameplay_inputs_enabled and action in GAMEPLAY_ACTIONS:\n\t\treturn false\n\treturn Input.is_action_just_pressed(action)\n\n## Returns the analog strength (0.0 - 1.0) of the specified action.\nfunc get_action_strength(action: String) -> float:\n\tif not _gameplay_inputs_enabled and action in GAMEPLAY_ACTIONS:","numLines":30,"startLine":55,"totalLines":206}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KLymGiasqY4AzNqQ4395tw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so `set_gameplay_inputs_enabled()` just sets a flag. It doesn't pause the tree. So tweens should still run.\n\nLet me think about this more. Let me look at the `_on_fuel_changed` callback. When `initiate_travel()` calls `FuelSystem.consume_fuel(cost)`, it changes the fuel. This emits `fuel_changed`. The NavigationConsole has `FuelSystem.fuel_changed.connect(_on_fuel_changed)`. Let me check `_on_fuel_changed`:\n\n```gdscript\nfunc _on_fuel_changed(_current: float, _maximum: float) -> void:\n\n\n```\n\nThe wave 2 fix calls `_close_for_travel()` BEFORE `initiate_travel()`. So by the time `initiate_travel()` runs and consumes fuel, `_is_open` is `false`. So `_on_fuel_changed` is a no-op. This was the wave 2 fix.\n\nBut wait, let me check `_close_for_travel()` more carefully...\n\nDefining the callback logic...\n\nSo `_close_for_travel()` sets `_is_open` to false, captures the mouse, animates the panel closed with a tween that fades out the dim rect and main panel, and then hides the entire NavigationConsole node. That's the key—`visible = false` means the node itself is hidden, so even if fuel changes fire events, nothing would refresh anyway.\n\nBut I'm wondering if hiding the CanvasLayer actually stops its processing, or if it just makes it invisible. And more importantly, I should check whether anything is listening to that `panel_closed` signal that gets emitted.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":566,"cache_read_input_tokens":71174,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":566},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"3d1a0e81-486e-4a4e-a07d-eabf644171d3"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KLymGiasqY4AzNqQ4395tw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01A9JzJDj88Pp542v1HLrZp7","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"panel_closed","glob":"*.gd","output_mode":"content","-n":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_toke