repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd:3:## Emits fuel_changed on any fuel change, fuel_low when crossing below 25% capacity,\nC:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd:11:signal fuel_changed(current: float, maximum: float)\nC:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd:46:## Emits fuel_changed every call.\nC:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd:54:\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\nC:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd:100:\t\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\nC:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd:129:\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)","numLines":37}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XDpNMqEcwGrEeMuiWsxdLc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at FuelSystem.consume_fuel() to understand the flow fully.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3119,"cache_read_input_tokens":79139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3119},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"09f83796-923b-4e0c-9a73-5047b8bffb44"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XDpNMqEcwGrEeMuiWsxdLc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EudThVHG1fcjKqgpvsQoNQ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3119,"cache_read_input_tokens":79139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3119},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"df76be40-3cc5-4522-8012-f9c98bc47125"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EudThVHG1fcjKqgpvsQoNQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Ship fuel system autoload: manages the fuel tank, consumption on travel,\n     2→## refueling from inventory Fuel Cells, and travel feasibility checks.\n     3→## Emits fuel_changed on any fuel change, fuel_low when crossing below 25% capacity,\n     4→## and fuel_empty when the tank reaches zero.\n     5→## Ticket: TICKET-0158\n     6→class_name FuelSystemType\n     7→extends Node\n     8→\n     9→# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n    10→## Emitted whenever fuel_current changes (consume or refuel).\n    11→signal fuel_changed(current: float, maximum: float)\n    12→## Emitted once when fuel first drops to or below 25% of max capacity.\n    13→## Resets when fuel rises above the threshold (e.g. after refueling).\n    14→signal fuel_low\n    15→## Emitted once when fuel first reaches exactly zero.\n    16→## Resets when fuel rises above zero (e.g. after refueling).\n    17→signal fuel_empty\n    18→\n    19→# ── Exported Variables ────────────────────────────────────\n    20→## Maximum tank capacity. Set from FuelSystemDefs so it can be overridden in editor.\n    21→@export var fuel_max: float = FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_TANK_CAPACITY\n    22→\n    23→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    24→var _fuel_current: float = 0.0\n    25→## Tracks whether the fuel_low signal has already been emitted for the current\n    26→## below-threshold period. Reset when fuel rises above threshold.\n    27→var _low_signal_emitted: bool = false\n    28→## Tracks whether the fuel_empty signal has already been emitted for the current\n    29→## empty period. Reset when fuel rises above zero.\n    30→var _empty_signal_emitted: bool = false\n    31→\n    32→# ── Public Variables ──────────────────────────────────────\n    33→## Current fuel level. Read-only externally — mutate via consume_fuel / refuel.\n    34→var fuel_current: float:\n    35→\tget:\n    36→\t\treturn _fuel_current\n    37→\n    38→# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\n    39→func _ready() -> void:\n    40→\t_fuel_current = fuel_max\n    41→\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: initialized (fuel=%.1f/%.1f)\" % [_fuel_current, fuel_max])\n    42→\n    43→# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n    44→\n    45→## Deducts fuel from the tank by the given amount. Clamps to zero.\n    46→## Emits fuel_changed every call.\n    47→## Emits fuel_low (once per threshold crossing) when fuel drops to ≤25% capacity.\n    48→## Emits fuel_empty (once per depletion) when fuel reaches 0.\n    49→func consume_fuel(amount: float) -> void:\n    50→\tif amount <= 0.0:\n    51→\t\treturn\n    52→\tvar threshold: float = fuel_max * FuelSystemDefs.LOW_FUEL_THRESHOLD_PERCENT\n    53→\t_fuel_current = maxf(_fuel_current - amount, 0.0)\n    54→\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\n    55→\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: consumed %.1f fuel (current=%.1f/%.1f)\" % [\n    56→\t\tamount, _fuel_current, fuel_max])\n    57→\tif _fuel_current <= threshold and not _low_signal_emitted:\n    58→\t\t_low_signal_emitted = true\n    59→\t\tfuel_low.emit()\n    60→\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: LOW FUEL — %.1f/%.1f (%.0f%%)\" % [\n    61→\t\t\t_fuel_current, fuel_max, _fuel_current / fuel_max * 100.0])\n    62→\tif _fuel_current <= 0.0 and not _empty_signal_emitted:\n    63→\t\t_empty_signal_emitted = true\n    64→\t\tfuel_empty.emit()\n    65→\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: FUEL EMPTY — tank depleted\")\n    66→\n    67→## Converts up to fuel_cells Fuel Cells from the player inventory into fuel units.\n    68→## Removes consumed Fuel Cells from PlayerInventory.\n    69→## Does not exceed tank capacity.\n    70→## Returns the number of Fuel Cells actually consumed.\n    71→func refuel(fuel_cells: int) -> int:\n    72→\tif fuel_cells <= 0:\n    73→\t\treturn 0\n    74→\tvar available: int = PlayerInventory.get_total_count(ResourceDefs.ResourceType.FUEL_CELL)\n    75→\tvar to_consume: int = mini(fuel_cells, available)\n    76→\tif to_consume <= 0:\n    77→\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: refuel requested but no Fuel Cells in inventory\")\n    78→\t\treturn 0\n    79→\t# Calculate how many cells are actually needed to fill the tank\n    80→\tvar space_remaining: float = fuel_max - _fuel_current\n    81→\tif space_remaining <= 0.0:\n    82→\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: refuel skipped — tank already full\")\n    83→\t\treturn 0\n    84→\tvar cells_needed_for_full: int = ceili(space_remaining / FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_CELL_UNITS)\n    85→\tto_consume = mini(to_consume, cells_needed_for_full)\n    86→\t# Remove cells from inventory (consume any purity, lowest first)\n    87→\tvar removed: int = _remove_fuel_cells(to_consume)\n    88→\tif removed <= 0:\n    89→\t\treturn 0\n    90→\tvar fuel_gained: float = removed * FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_CELL_UNITS\n    91→\tvar previous_fuel: float = _fuel_current\n    92→\t_fuel_current = minf(_fuel_current + fuel_gained, fuel_max)\n    93→\t# Reset signal flags when fuel rises above thresholds\n    94→\tvar threshold: float = fuel_max * FuelSystemDefs.LOW_FUEL_THRESHOLD_PERCENT\n    95→\tif _fuel_current > threshold:\n    96→\t\t_low_signal_emitted = false\n    97→\tif _fuel_current > 0.0:\n    98→\t\t_empty_signal_emitted = false\n    99→\tif _fuel_current != previous_fuel:\n   100→\t\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\n   101→\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: refueled %d Fuel Cells (+%.1f fuel) (current=%.1f/%.1f)\" % [\n   102→\t\tremoved, fuel_gained, _fuel_current, fuel_max])\n   103→\treturn removed\n   104→\n   105→## Calculates the fuel cost for a jump of the given distance with the given ship weight.\n   106→## Formula: distance * ship_weight * FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_COST_MULTIPLIER\n   107→func calculate_cost(distance: float, ship_weight: float) -> float:\n   108→\treturn distance * ship_weight * FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_COST_MULTIPLIER\n   109→\n   110→## Returns true if the current tank has enough fuel to make the jump.\n   111→## distance and ship_weight are used to compute the cost via calculate_cost.\n   112→func can_travel(distance: float, ship_weight: float) -> bool:\n   113→\tvar cost: float = calculate_cost(distance, ship_weight)\n   114→\treturn _fuel_current >= cost\n   115→\n   116→## Calculates the current total ship weight.\n   117→## Weight = BASE_SHIP_WEIGHT + (installed module count * WEIGHT_PER_MODULE) + (total inventory item count * WEIGHT_PER_INVENTORY_ITEM)\n   118→func calculate_ship_weight() -> int:\n   119→\tvar module_weight: int = ModuleManager.get_installed_count() * FuelSystemDefs.WEIGHT_PER_MODULE\n   120→\tvar inventory_weight: int = _get_total_inventory_items() * FuelSystemDefs.WEIGHT_PER_INVENTORY_ITEM\n   121→\treturn FuelSystemDefs.BASE_SHIP_WEIGHT + module_weight + inventory_weight\n   122→\n   123→## Resets fuel to maximum capacity. Clears signal-emitted flags.\n   124→## Used for new-game initialization and test teardown.\n   125→func reset_to_full() -> void:\n   126→\t_fuel_current = fuel_max\n   127→\t_low_signal_emitted = false\n   128→\t_empty_signal_emitted = false\n   129→\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\n   130→\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: reset to full (%.1f/%.1f)\" % [_fuel_current, fuel_max])\n   131→\n   132→# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n   133→\n   134→## Returns the total count of all items across all non-NONE resource types in inventory.\n   135→func _get_total_inventory_items() -> int:\n   136→\tvar total: int = 0\n   137→\tfor resource_type_value: int in ResourceDefs.ResourceType.values():\n   138→\t\tvar resource_type: ResourceDefs.ResourceType = resource_type_value as ResourceDefs.ResourceType\n   139→\t\tif resource_type == ResourceDefs.ResourceType.NONE:\n   140→\t\t\tcontinue\n   141→\t\ttotal += PlayerInventory.get_total_count(resource_type)\n   142→\treturn total\n   143→\n   144→## Removes a specified number of Fuel Cells from inventory, consuming lowest purity first.\n   145→## Returns the quantity actually removed.\n   146→func _remove_fuel_cells(quantity: int) -> int:\n   147→\tvar remaining: int = quantity\n   148→\tfor purity_value: int in ResourceDefs.Purity.values():\n   149→\t\tif remaining <= 0:\n   150→\t\t\tbreak\n   151→\t\tvar purity: ResourceDefs.Purity = purity_value as ResourceDefs.Purity\n   152→\t\tvar available: int = PlayerInventory.get_count(ResourceDefs.ResourceType.FUEL_CELL, purity)\n   153→\t\tif available > 0:\n   154→\t\t\tvar to_remove: int = mini(remaining, available)\n   155→\t\t\tvar removed: int = PlayerInventory.remove_item(\n   156→\t\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.FUEL_CELL, purity, to_remove)\n   157→\t\t\tremaining -= removed\n   158→\treturn quantity - remaining\n   159→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"bd4169d4-8677-4dab-89f2-4ca992aa1594","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\systems\\fuel_system.gd","content":"## Ship fuel system autoload: manages the fuel tank, consumption on travel,\n## refueling from inventory Fuel Cells, and travel feasibility checks.\n## Emits fuel_changed on any fuel change, fuel_low when crossing below 25% capacity,\n## and fuel_empty when the tank reaches zero.\n## Ticket: TICKET-0158\nclass_name FuelSystemType\nextends Node\n\n# ── Signals ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n## Emitted whenever fuel_current changes (consume or refuel).\nsignal fuel_changed(current: float, maximum: float)\n## Emitted once when fuel first drops to or below 25% of max capacity.\n## Resets when fuel rises above the threshold (e.g. after refueling).\nsignal fuel_low\n## Emitted once when fuel first reaches exactly zero.\n## Resets when fuel rises above zero (e.g. after refueling).\nsignal fuel_empty\n\n# ── Exported Variables ────────────────────────────────────\n## Maximum tank capacity. Set from FuelSystemDefs so it can be overridden in editor.\n@export var fuel_max: float = FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_TANK_CAPACITY\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\nvar _fuel_current: float = 0.0\n## Tracks whether the fuel_low signal has already been emitted for the current\n## below-threshold period. Reset when fuel rises above threshold.\nvar _low_signal_emitted: bool = false\n## Tracks whether the fuel_empty signal has already been emitted for the current\n## empty period. Reset when fuel rises above zero.\nvar _empty_signal_emitted: bool = false\n\n# ── Public Variables ──────────────────────────────────────\n## Current fuel level. Read-only externally — mutate via consume_fuel / refuel.\nvar fuel_current: float:\n\tget:\n\t\treturn _fuel_current\n\n# ── Built-in Virtual Methods ──────────────────────────────\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\t_fuel_current = fuel_max\n\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: initialized (fuel=%.1f/%.1f)\" % [_fuel_current, fuel_max])\n\n# ── Public Methods ────────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Deducts fuel from the tank by the given amount. Clamps to zero.\n## Emits fuel_changed every call.\n## Emits fuel_low (once per threshold crossing) when fuel drops to ≤25% capacity.\n## Emits fuel_empty (once per depletion) when fuel reaches 0.\nfunc consume_fuel(amount: float) -> void:\n\tif amount <= 0.0:\n\t\treturn\n\tvar threshold: float = fuel_max * FuelSystemDefs.LOW_FUEL_THRESHOLD_PERCENT\n\t_fuel_current = maxf(_fuel_current - amount, 0.0)\n\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\n\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: consumed %.1f fuel (current=%.1f/%.1f)\" % [\n\t\tamount, _fuel_current, fuel_max])\n\tif _fuel_current <= threshold and not _low_signal_emitted:\n\t\t_low_signal_emitted = true\n\t\tfuel_low.emit()\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: LOW FUEL — %.1f/%.1f (%.0f%%)\" % [\n\t\t\t_fuel_current, fuel_max, _fuel_current / fuel_max * 100.0])\n\tif _fuel_current <= 0.0 and not _empty_signal_emitted:\n\t\t_empty_signal_emitted = true\n\t\tfuel_empty.emit()\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: FUEL EMPTY — tank depleted\")\n\n## Converts up to fuel_cells Fuel Cells from the player inventory into fuel units.\n## Removes consumed Fuel Cells from PlayerInventory.\n## Does not exceed tank capacity.\n## Returns the number of Fuel Cells actually consumed.\nfunc refuel(fuel_cells: int) -> int:\n\tif fuel_cells <= 0:\n\t\treturn 0\n\tvar available: int = PlayerInventory.get_total_count(ResourceDefs.ResourceType.FUEL_CELL)\n\tvar to_consume: int = mini(fuel_cells, available)\n\tif to_consume <= 0:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: refuel requested but no Fuel Cells in inventory\")\n\t\treturn 0\n\t# Calculate how many cells are actually needed to fill the tank\n\tvar space_remaining: float = fuel_max - _fuel_current\n\tif space_remaining <= 0.0:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: refuel skipped — tank already full\")\n\t\treturn 0\n\tvar cells_needed_for_full: int = ceili(space_remaining / FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_CELL_UNITS)\n\tto_consume = mini(to_consume, cells_needed_for_full)\n\t# Remove cells from inventory (consume any purity, lowest first)\n\tvar removed: int = _remove_fuel_cells(to_consume)\n\tif removed <= 0:\n\t\treturn 0\n\tvar fuel_gained: float = removed * FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_CELL_UNITS\n\tvar previous_fuel: float = _fuel_current\n\t_fuel_current = minf(_fuel_current + fuel_gained, fuel_max)\n\t# Reset signal flags when fuel rises above thresholds\n\tvar threshold: float = fuel_max * FuelSystemDefs.LOW_FUEL_THRESHOLD_PERCENT\n\tif _fuel_current > threshold:\n\t\t_low_signal_emitted = false\n\tif _fuel_current > 0.0:\n\t\t_empty_signal_emitted = false\n\tif _fuel_current != previous_fuel:\n\t\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\n\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: refueled %d Fuel Cells (+%.1f fuel) (current=%.1f/%.1f)\" % [\n\t\tremoved, fuel_gained, _fuel_current, fuel_max])\n\treturn removed\n\n## Calculates the fuel cost for a jump of the given distance with the given ship weight.\n## Formula: distance * ship_weight * FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_COST_MULTIPLIER\nfunc calculate_cost(distance: float, ship_weight: float) -> float:\n\treturn distance * ship_weight * FuelSystemDefs.FUEL_COST_MULTIPLIER\n\n## Returns true if the current tank has enough fuel to make the jump.\n## distance and ship_weight are used to compute the cost via calculate_cost.\nfunc can_travel(distance: float, ship_weight: float) -> bool:\n\tvar cost: float = calculate_cost(distance, ship_weight)\n\treturn _fuel_current >= cost\n\n## Calculates the current total ship weight.\n## Weight = BASE_SHIP_WEIGHT + (installed module count * WEIGHT_PER_MODULE) + (total inventory item count * WEIGHT_PER_INVENTORY_ITEM)\nfunc calculate_ship_weight() -> int:\n\tvar module_weight: int = ModuleManager.get_installed_count() * FuelSystemDefs.WEIGHT_PER_MODULE\n\tvar inventory_weight: int = _get_total_inventory_items() * FuelSystemDefs.WEIGHT_PER_INVENTORY_ITEM\n\treturn FuelSystemDefs.BASE_SHIP_WEIGHT + module_weight + inventory_weight\n\n## Resets fuel to maximum capacity. Clears signal-emitted flags.\n## Used for new-game initialization and test teardown.\nfunc reset_to_full() -> void:\n\t_fuel_current = fuel_max\n\t_low_signal_emitted = false\n\t_empty_signal_emitted = false\n\tfuel_changed.emit(_fuel_current, fuel_max)\n\tGlobal.log(\"FuelSystem: reset to full (%.1f/%.1f)\" % [_fuel_current, fuel_max])\n\n# ── Private Methods ───────────────────────────────────────\n\n## Returns the total count of all items across all non-NONE resource types in inventory.\nfunc _get_total_inventory_items() -> int:\n\tvar total: int = 0\n\tfor resource_type_value: int in ResourceDefs.ResourceType.values():\n\t\tvar resource_type: ResourceDefs.ResourceType = resource_type_value as ResourceDefs.ResourceType\n\t\tif resource_type == ResourceDefs.ResourceType.NONE:\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\ttotal += PlayerInventory.get_total_count(resource_type)\n\treturn total\n\n## Removes a specified number of Fuel Cells from inventory, consuming lowest purity first.\n## Returns the quantity actually removed.\nfunc _remove_fuel_cells(quantity: int) -> int:\n\tvar remaining: int = quantity\n\tfor purity_value: int in ResourceDefs.Purity.values():\n\t\tif remaining <= 0:\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\tvar purity: ResourceDefs.Purity = purity_value as ResourceDefs.Purity\n\t\tvar available: int = PlayerInventory.get_count(ResourceDefs.ResourceType.FUEL_CELL, purity)\n\t\tif available > 0:\n\t\t\tvar to_remove: int = mini(remaining, available)\n\t\t\tvar removed: int = PlayerInventory.remove_item(\n\t\t\t\tResourceDefs.ResourceType.FUEL_CELL, purity, to_remove)\n\t\t\tremaining -= removed\n\treturn quantity - remaining\n","numLines":159,"startLine":1,"totalLines":159}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Wue8ezfTao7jFyfAh9dxoJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full flow. `consume_fuel()` emits `fuel_changed`. The NavigationConsole's `_on_fuel_changed` is connected to this signal. But since `_is_open` is `false` (set by `_close_for_travel()` before `initiate_travel()`), the callback is a no-op.\n\nLet me now look at another angle. What if the problem is with the `_close_for_travel()` → `_animate_close()` interaction? Specifically, `_animate_close()` creates a tween on the NavigationConsole with `visible = false` as a callback. But `visible = false` on a CanvasLayer... let me check if this could cause any issues for the TravelSequenceManager.\n\n\nThey're separate nodes, so the NavigationConsole's visibility shouldn't affect TravelSequenceManager. But looking at `_animate_close()` more carefully, it's fading out the dim rect and main panel over 0.15 seconds...\n\nActually, I think I need to step back and look at what's actually happening. The player reports being visibly locked in place with no fade-to-black and no scene change, which means inputs are disabled but nothing else is progressing. Let me trace through whether `_on_travel_completed` is even firing in the first place. I need to trace whether `panel_closed` is being connected to anything at runtime that might be interfering with the travel sequence. Let me search for any connections to that signal outside of the test code.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2926,"cache_read_input_tokens":82258,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2926},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"b9d7fb0a-6316-4a1b-a08c-e360d966afe1"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Wue8ezfTao7jFyfAh9dxoJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01W7t5o5RwkxQGj5Zrj4toh9","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"panel_closed\\.connect","glob":"*.gd","output_mode":"content","-n":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2926,"cache_read_input_tokens":82258,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2926},"output_tokens":8,"s