s://autoloads/Global.gd\"\n    20→InputManager=\"*res://autoloads/InputManager.gd\"\n    21→AgentLogger=\"*res://autoloads/AgentLogger.gd\"\n    22→SuitBattery=\"*res://scripts/systems/suit_battery.gd\"\n    23→PlayerInventory=\"*res://scripts/systems/inventory.gd\"\n    24→DepositRegistry=\"*res://scripts/systems/deposit_registry.gd\"\n    25→ShipState=\"*res://scripts/systems/ship_state.gd\"\n    26→ModuleManager=\"*res://scripts/systems/module_manager.gd\"\n    27→Recycler=\"*res://scripts/systems/recycler.gd\"\n    28→TechTree=\"*res://autoloads/tech_tree.gd\"\n    29→HeadLamp=\"*res://scripts/systems/head_lamp.gd\"\n    30→Fabricator=\"*res://scripts/systems/fabricator.gd\"\n    31→AutomationHub=\"*res://scripts/systems/automation_hub.gd\"\n    32→FuelSystem=\"*res://scripts/systems/fuel_system.gd\"\n    33→NavigationSystem=\"*res://scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd\"\n    34→ResourceRespawnSystem=\"*res://scripts/systems/resource_respawn_system.gd\"\n    35→GDAIMCPRuntime=\"*res://addons/gdai-mcp-plugin-godot/gdai_mcp_runtime.gd\"\n    36→\n    37→[editor_plugins]\n    38→\n    39→enabled=PackedStringArray(\"res://addons/gdai-mcp-plugin-godot/plugin.cfg\", \"res://addons/hammer_forge_tests/plugin.cfg\")\n    40→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"c84db153-b2ed-442d-ad9e-447ba5cc035c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\project.godot","content":"[autoload]\n\nGlobal=\"*res://autoloads/Global.gd\"\nInputManager=\"*res://autoloads/InputManager.gd\"\nAgentLogger=\"*res://autoloads/AgentLogger.gd\"\nSuitBattery=\"*res://scripts/systems/suit_battery.gd\"\nPlayerInventory=\"*res://scripts/systems/inventory.gd\"\nDepositRegistry=\"*res://scripts/systems/deposit_registry.gd\"\nShipState=\"*res://scripts/systems/ship_state.gd\"\nModuleManager=\"*res://scripts/systems/module_manager.gd\"\nRecycler=\"*res://scripts/systems/recycler.gd\"\nTechTree=\"*res://autoloads/tech_tree.gd\"\nHeadLamp=\"*res://scripts/systems/head_lamp.gd\"\nFabricator=\"*res://scripts/systems/fabricator.gd\"\nAutomationHub=\"*res://scripts/systems/automation_hub.gd\"\nFuelSystem=\"*res://scripts/systems/fuel_system.gd\"\nNavigationSystem=\"*res://scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd\"\nResourceRespawnSystem=\"*res://scripts/systems/resource_respawn_system.gd\"\nGDAIMCPRuntime=\"*res://addons/gdai-mcp-plugin-godot/gdai_mcp_runtime.gd\"\n\n[editor_plugins]\n\nenabled=PackedStringArray(\"res://addons/gdai-mcp-plugin-godot/plugin.cfg\", \"res://addons/hammer_forge_tests/plugin.cfg\")\n","numLines":24,"startLine":17,"totalLines":40}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FtxhqKbr9iqNqfggahiVLH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, `NavigationSystem` is an autoload. Its class name is `NavigationSystemType` but the autoload name is `NavigationSystem`. In GDScript, you reference autoloads by their autoload name. So `NavigationSystem.travel_completed.connect(...)` and `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(...)` both refer to the same autoload instance. That's correct.\n\nNow, let me think about one more thing. The `NavigationSystemType` class has `class_name NavigationSystemType`. But the autoload is named `NavigationSystem`. In GDScript, when you use `NavigationSystem`, you're referring to the autoload singleton, not the class. The class is `NavigationSystemType`. So `NavigationSystem.travel_completed` accesses the singleton's signal. This is correct.\n\n\nBoth the signal connection and the method call are targeting the same autoload singleton, so that should work fine. Let me shift focus and examine how Godot 4 handles `await` behavior in signal handlers more carefully.\n\nWhen a signal fires and triggers a connected method containing `await`, that method runs as a coroutine—it starts executing, suspends at the first `await`, and the signal emission returns. In this case, `_on_travel_completed` would start, hit `await _fade_out()`, and suspend while the fade animation runs on its tween for 0.5 seconds before resuming.\n\nThis should all work correctly, but what if there's a silent runtime error? If `create_tween()` fails—say, because the node isn't in the tree despite the `is_inside_tree()` check—the coroutine could silently die. But GDScript is single-threaded, so there's no race condition there. Looking at `_fade_out` again, if `_fade_rect` exists and the node is in the tree, it should create the tween and await its completion without issue.\n\nEven if `_fade_rect.modulate.a` is already at 1.0, the tween would still run for the full duration and emit `finished`, so that's not the problem either. Let me check what the initial modulate value actually is.\n\nNow I'm looking at the `execute_biome_swap` method to see if the issue might be there instead of in the fade logic.\n\nContinuing with the rest of the method... I'm checking whether `_biome_container` could be null. It gets assigned in the `setup()` method, so if setup was called properly, it should be fine. But let me trace through the initialization to make sure that's not where things are breaking down. Continuing to trace through the cleanup logic, I'm seeing that `_clear_biome_container()` iterates through children, removes them, and queues them for deletion, then unregisters any deposits from the registry and nulls out the current biome node. The real question is whether something in a child's `_exit_tree()` callback could interfere with the tween or travel sequence that's happening concurrently.\n\nBut wait—`_clear_biome_container()` is called inside `execute_biome_swap()`, which only runs after `await _fade_out()` completes, so if the fade isn't happening, the problem has to be earlier in the sequence. Let me reconsider what \"no fade\" actually means: either the overlay isn't visible, the tween never starts, or something's layered on top blocking it. The NavigationConsole is a CanvasLayer with layer 2, while the TravelFadeLayer is layer 10, so it should be on top—and besides, the console gets hidden by `_animate_close()` anyway.\n\nI've been going in circles. Let me check what actually changed in wave 2 and trace through the exact sequence of events, starting with what the activity log says about `_on_confirm_pressed()` calling `close_panel()` after `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()`, which triggers the `travel_completed` signal during that same call.\n\nThe root cause is that `_on_travel_completed` suspends waiting for the fade animation, but then `close_panel()` immediately re-enables inputs, undoing what the travel sequence just disabled. The fix was to create a separate `_close_for_travel()` method that closes the panel without touching input state, letting the TravelSequenceManager handle that when it finishes. They also reordered the calls so the panel closes before travel initiates, preventing the fuel consumption callback from updating a UI that's already closing. The original order in wave 1 had the transition working, but inputs were being re-enabled during it. Wave 2 fixed the input issue by reordering the calls and creating `_close_for_travel()`, but that change somehow broke the transition entirely. I need to figure out what the reordering actually changed in the execution flow.\n\nLooking at the before and after: originally `initiate_travel()` was called first (which emits the signal that starts the fade-out), then `close_panel()` re-enabled inputs. Now `_close_for_travel()` runs first and emits `panel_closed`, then `initiate_travel()` is called. The key question is whether something in `_close_for_travel()` is preventing the travel signal from firing or being received.\n\nExamining `_close_for_travel()` implementation...\n\nit just sets the flag, captures the mouse, animates the panel closing, and emits the signal. But wait—`_animate_close()` creates a tween that fades out the panel and then sets visibility to false. In Godot 4, when you create a tween without specifying a target, it might be using the node's default tween context, and if that tween is somehow interfering with the signal flow or the subsequent travel sequence...\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The tween just hides the UI layer. The callback runs immediately on the next frame, setting `visible = false`. That shouldn't affect TravelSequenceManager at all. I'm going in circles here—let me look at what actually happens after the panel closes. So in Godot 4, `create_tween()` doesn't actually kill previous tweens like it did in Godot 3—multiple tweens can run independently on the same node, so there's no conflict between the NavigationConsole and TravelSequenceManager tweens. Let me step back and look at this from a different angle.\n\nComparing the two close methods, I notice `_close_for_travel()` is missing the InputManager call that `close_panel()` has, but otherwise they're nearly identical in structure.\n\nLet me step back and look at the actual test coverage for the travel sequence to understand what's being validated.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":810,"cache_read_input_tokens":95877,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":810},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"8b744938-f990-416d-9a42-c491a7a586d3"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FtxhqKbr9iqNqfggahiVLH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016jHyK1P5qmNK2CoGzKJR4V","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\tests\\test_travel_sequence_unit.gd"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":810,"cache_read_input_tokens":95877,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":810},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"cf9b2885-f841-4fc7-8d49-2acd824eb2b3"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016jHyK1P5qmNK2CoGzKJR4V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Unit tests for the travel sequence system. Verifies biome creation by ID,\n     2→## transition state management, signal emissions, input toggling, and error\n     3→## handling during inter-biome travel. Covers TICKET-0168 acceptance criteria:\n     4→## scene transition completes, player position valid after arrival,\n     5→## biome_changed signal fired, input re-enabled.\n     6→##\n     7→## Coverage target: 75% (per docs/studio/tdd-process-m8.md — biome travel mechanics)\n     8→## Ticket: TICKET-0168\n     9→class_name TestTravelSequenceUnit\n    10→extends TestSuite\n    11→\n    12→\n    13→# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n    14→\n    15→var _manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\n    16→var _container: Node3D = null\n    17→var _spy: SignalSpy = null\n    18→\n    19→\n    20→# ── Setup / Teardown ──────────────────────────────────────\n    21→\n    22→func before_each() -> void:\n    23→\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n    24→\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n    25→\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n    26→\tShipState.reset()\n    27→\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n    28→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n    29→\n    30→\t_container = Node3D.new()\n    31→\t_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n    32→\t_manager.setup(null, null, _container)\n    33→\n    34→\t_spy = SignalSpy.new()\n    35→\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_started\")\n    36→\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_completed\")\n    37→\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_completed\")\n    38→\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"biome_changed\")\n    39→\n    40→\n    41→func after_each() -> void:\n    42→\t_spy.clear()\n    43→\t_spy = null\n    44→\n    45→\tif _manager:\n    46→\t\t_manager.teardown()\n    47→\t\t_manager.free()\n    48→\t\t_manager = null\n    49→\n    50→\tif _container:\n    51→\t\tfor child: Node in _container.get_children():\n    52→\t\t\tchild.free()\n    53→\t\t_container.free()\n    54→\t\t_container = null\n    55→\n    56→\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n    57→\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n    58→\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n    59→\tShipState.reset()\n    60→\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n    61→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n    62→\n    63→\n    64→# ── Test Registration ─────────────────────────────────────\n    65→\n    66→func register_tests() -> void:\n    67→\t# Biome creation by ID\n    68→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node)\n    69→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node)\n    70→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node)\n    71→\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null\", _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null)\n    72→\n    73→\t# Initial state\n    74→\tadd_test(\"initial_is_transitioning_is_false\", _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false)\n    75→\n    76→\t# Travel sequence signal flow\n    77→\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel\", _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel)\n    78→\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap\", _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap)\n    79→\tadd_test(\"biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel\", _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel)\n    80→\n    81→\t# Input management\n    82→\tadd_test(\"input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes\", _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes)\n    83→\n    84→\t# Biome swap\n    85→\tadd_test(\"current_biome_node_updated_after_travel\", _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel)\n    86→\tadd_test(\"biome_container_has_child_after_travel\", _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel)\n    87→\tadd_test(\"old_biome_removed_on_second_travel\", _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel)\n    88→\n    89→\t# Player/ship spawn position\n    90→\tadd_test(\"get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n    91→\tadd_test(\"get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n    92→\n    93→\t# Error handling\n    94→\tadd_test(\"invalid_biome_swap_returns_false\", _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false)\n    95→\tadd_test(\"input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap\", _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap)\n    96→\tadd_test(\"sequential_travel_works_correctly\", _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly)\n    97→\n    98→\n    99→# ── Test Methods: Biome Creation ─────────────────────────\n   100→\n   101→func _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node() -> void:\n   102→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"shattered_flats\")\n   103→\tassert_not_null(node,\n   104→\t\t\"create_biome_node('shattered_flats') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n   105→\tif node:\n   106→\t\tnode.free()\n   107→\n   108→\n   109→func _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node() -> void:\n   110→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n   111→\tassert_not_null(node,\n   112→\t\t\"create_biome_node('rock_warrens') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n   113→\tif node:\n   114→\t\tnode.free()\n   115→\n   116→\n   117→func _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node() -> void:\n   118→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"debris_field\")\n   119→\tassert_not_null(node,\n   120→\t\t\"create_biome_node('debris_field') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n   121→\tif node:\n   122→\t\tnode.free()\n   123→\n   124→\n   125→func _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null() -> void:\n   126→\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"unknown_void\")\n   127→\tassert_null(node,\n   128→\t\t\"create_biome_node with invalid ID should return null\")\n   129→\n   130→\n   131→# ── Test Methods: Initial State ──────────────────────────\n   132→\n   133→func _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false() -> void:\n   134→\tassert_false(_manager.is_transitioning(),\n   135→\t\t\"TravelSequenceManager should not be transitioning initially\")\n   136→\n   137→\n   138→# ── Test Methods: Signal Flow ────────────────────────────\n   139→\n   140→func _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel() -> void:\n   141→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   142→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_started\",\n   143→\t\t\"travel_sequence_started should emit when NavigationSystem.travel_completed fires\")\n   144→\n   145→\n   146→func _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap() -> void:\n   147→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   148→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_completed\",\n   149→\t\t\"travel_sequence_completed should emit after biome swap finishes\")\n   150→\n   151→\n   152→func _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel() -> void:\n   153→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   154→\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"biome_changed\",\n   155→\t\t\"NavigationSystem.biome_changed should fire on successful travel\")\n   156→\n   157→\n   158→# ── Test Methods: Input Management ───────────────────────\n   159→\n   160→func _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes() -> void:\n   161→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   162→\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n   163→\t\t\"Gameplay inputs should be re-enabled after travel sequence completes\")\n   164→\n   165→\n   166→# ── Test Methods: Biome Swap ─────────────────────────────\n   167→\n   168→func _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel() -> void:\n   169→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   170→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   171→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   172→\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after travel completes\")\n   173→\n   174→\n   175→func _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel() -> void:\n   176→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   177→\tassert_true(_container.get_child_count() > 0,\n   178→\t\t\"Biome container should have a child biome node after travel\")\n   179→\n   180→\n   181→func _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel() -> void:\n   182→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   183→\tvar first_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   184→\tassert_not_null(first_biome,\n   185→\t\t\"First biome node should exist after first travel\")\n   186→\n   187→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n   188→\t# Container should have exactly one child (the new biome)\n   189→\tassert_equal(_container.get_child_count(), 1,\n   190→\t\t\"Container should have exactly one biome node after second travel\")\n   191→\tvar second_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   192→\tassert_not_null(second_biome,\n   193→\t\t\"Second biome node should exist after second travel\")\n   194→\n   195→\n   196→# ── Test Methods: Spawn Positions ────────────────────────\n   197→\n   198→func _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n   199→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n   200→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   201→\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n   202→\tif biome_node:\n   203→\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n   204→\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n   205→\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n   206→\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node)\n   207→\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n   208→\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n   209→\t\t\t\"Player spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n   210→\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n   211→\n   212→\n   213→func _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n   214→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n   215→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   216→\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n   217→\tif biome_node:\n   218→\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n   219→\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n   220→\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n   221→\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node)\n   222→\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n   223→\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n   224→\t\t\t\"Ship spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n   225→\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n   226→\n   227→\n   228→# ── Test Methods: Error Handling ─────────────────────────\n   229→\n   230→func _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false() -> void:\n   231→\tvar result: bool = _manager.execute_biome_swap(\"nonexistent_biome\")\n   232→\tassert_false(result,\n   233→\t\t\"execute_biome_swap with invalid biome should return false\")\n   234→\n   235→\n   236→func _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap() -> void:\n   237→\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n   238→\t_manager.execute_biome_swap(\"invalid_zone\")\n   239→\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n   240→\t\t\"Input should remain enabled after a failed biome swap\")\n   241→\n   242→\n   243→func _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly() -> void:\n   244→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n   245→\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"rock_warrens\",\n   246→\t\t\"Should be at rock_warrens after first travel\")\n   247→\n   248→\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n   249→\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"debris_field\",\n   250→\t\t\"Should be at debris_field after second travel\")\n   251→\n   252→\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n   253→\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n   254→\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after sequential travel\")\n   255→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"9f5be32a-228c-4cfc-ae7a-be9200610bd3","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\tests\\test_travel_sequence_unit.gd","content":"## Unit tests for the travel sequence system. Verifies biome creation by ID,\n## transition state management, signal emissions, input toggling, and error\n## handling during inter-biome travel. Covers TICKET-0168 acceptance criteria:\n## scene transition completes, player position valid after arrival,\n## biome_changed signal fired, input re-enabled.\n##\n## Coverage target: 75% (per docs/studio/tdd-process-m8.md — biome travel mechanics)\n## Ticket: TICKET-0168\nclass_name TestTravelSequenceUnit\nextends TestSuite\n\n\n# ── Private Variables ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nvar _manager: TravelSequenceManager = null\nvar _container: Node3D = null\nvar _spy: SignalSpy = null\n\n\n# ── Setup / Teardown ──────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc before_each() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n\tShipState.reset()\n\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\n\t_container = Node3D.new()\n\t_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n\t_manager.setup(null, null, _container)\n\n\t_spy = SignalSpy.new()\n\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_started\")\n\t_spy.watch(_manager, \"travel_sequence_completed\")\n\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"travel_completed\")\n\t_spy.watch(NavigationSystem, \"biome_changed\")\n\n\nfunc after_each() -> void:\n\t_spy.clear()\n\t_spy = null\n\n\tif _manager:\n\t\t_manager.teardown()\n\t\t_manager.free()\n\t\t_manager = null\n\n\tif _container:\n\t\tfor child: Node in _container.get_children():\n\t\t\tchild.free()\n\t\t_container.free()\n\t\t_container = null\n\n\tNavigationSystem.reset()\n\tFuelSystem.reset_to_full()\n\tPlayerInventory.clear_all()\n\tShipState.reset()\n\tResourceRespawnSystem.reset()\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\n\n# ── Test Registration ─────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunc register_tests() -> void:\n\t# Biome creation by ID\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node)\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node)\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node\", _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node)\n\tadd_test(\"create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null\", _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null)\n\n\t# Initial state\n\tadd_test(\"initial_is_transitioning_is_false\", _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false)\n\n\t# Travel sequence signal flow\n\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel\", _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel)\n\tadd_test(\"travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap\", _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap)\n\tadd_test(\"biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel\", _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel)\n\n\t# Input management\n\tadd_test(\"input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes\", _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes)\n\n\t# Biome swap\n\tadd_test(\"current_biome_node_updated_after_travel\", _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel)\n\tadd_test(\"biome_container_has_child_after_travel\", _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel)\n\tadd_test(\"old_biome_removed_on_second_travel\", _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel)\n\n\t# Player/ship spawn position\n\tadd_test(\"get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n\tadd_test(\"get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position\", _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position)\n\n\t# Error handling\n\tadd_test(\"invalid_biome_swap_returns_false\", _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false)\n\tadd_test(\"input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap\", _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap)\n\tadd_test(\"sequential_travel_works_correctly\", _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly)\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Biome Creation ─────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_shattered_flats_returns_node() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"shattered_flats\")\n\tassert_not_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node('shattered_flats') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n\tif node:\n\t\tnode.free()\n\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_rock_warrens_returns_node() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_not_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node('rock_warrens') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n\tif node:\n\t\tnode.free()\n\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_debris_field_returns_node() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"debris_field\")\n\tassert_not_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node('debris_field') should return a non-null Node3D\")\n\tif node:\n\t\tnode.free()\n\n\nfunc _test_create_biome_node_invalid_returns_null() -> void:\n\tvar node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"unknown_void\")\n\tassert_null(node,\n\t\t\"create_biome_node with invalid ID should return null\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Initial State ──────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_initial_is_transitioning_is_false() -> void:\n\tassert_false(_manager.is_transitioning(),\n\t\t\"TravelSequenceManager should not be transitioning initially\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Signal Flow ────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_travel_sequence_started_emitted_on_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_started\",\n\t\t\"travel_sequence_started should emit when NavigationSystem.travel_completed fires\")\n\n\nfunc _test_travel_sequence_completed_emitted_after_swap() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"travel_sequence_completed\",\n\t\t\"travel_sequence_completed should emit after biome swap finishes\")\n\n\nfunc _test_biome_changed_signal_fired_on_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_signal_emitted(_spy, \"biome_changed\",\n\t\t\"NavigationSystem.biome_changed should fire on successful travel\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Input Management ───────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_input_re_enabled_after_travel_completes() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n\t\t\"Gameplay inputs should be re-enabled after travel sequence completes\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Biome Swap ─────────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_current_biome_node_updated_after_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after travel completes\")\n\n\nfunc _test_biome_container_has_child_after_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_true(_container.get_child_count() > 0,\n\t\t\"Biome container should have a child biome node after travel\")\n\n\nfunc _test_old_biome_removed_on_second_travel() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tvar first_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(first_biome,\n\t\t\"First biome node should exist after first travel\")\n\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n\t# Container should have exactly one child (the new biome)\n\tassert_equal(_container.get_child_count(), 1,\n\t\t\"Container should have exactly one biome node after second travel\")\n\tvar second_biome: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(second_biome,\n\t\t\"Second biome node should exist after second travel\")\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Spawn Positions ────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_get_biome_player_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n\tif biome_node:\n\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_player_spawn(biome_node)\n\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n\t\t\t\"Player spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n\n\nfunc _test_get_biome_ship_spawn_returns_valid_position() -> void:\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = TravelSequenceManager.create_biome_node(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Biome node should be created for spawn point test\")\n\tif biome_node:\n\t\tadd_child(biome_node)\n\t\tif biome_node.has_method(\"generate\"):\n\t\t\tbiome_node.generate()\n\t\tvar spawn: Vector3 = TravelSequenceManager.get_biome_ship_spawn(biome_node)\n\t\tvar is_nonzero: bool = spawn != Vector3.ZERO\n\t\tassert_true(is_nonzero,\n\t\t\t\"Ship spawn position should be a non-zero Vector3\")\n\t\tbiome_node.queue_free()\n\n\n# ── Test Methods: Error Handling ─────────────────────────\n\nfunc _test_invalid_biome_swap_returns_false() -> void:\n\tvar result: bool = _manager.execute_biome_swap(\"nonexistent_biome\")\n\tassert_false(result,\n\t\t\"execute_biome_swap with invalid biome should return false\")\n\n\nfunc _test_input_stays_enabled_after_failed_swap() -> void:\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t_manager.execute_biome_swap(\"invalid_zone\")\n\tassert_true(InputManager.is_gameplay_inputs_enabled(),\n\t\t\"Input should remain enabled after a failed biome swap\")\n\n\nfunc _test_sequential_travel_works_correctly() -> void:\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"rock_warrens\")\n\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"rock_warrens\",\n\t\t\"Should be at rock_warrens after first travel\")\n\n\tNavigationSystem.initiate_travel(\"debris_field\")\n\tassert_equal(NavigationSystem.current_biome, \"debris_field\",\n\t\t\"Should be at debris_field after second travel\")\n\n\tvar biome_node: Node3D = _manager.get_current_biome_node()\n\tassert_not_null(biome_node,\n\t\t\"Current biome node should be set after sequential travel\")\n","numLines":255,"startLine":1,"totalLines":255}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GGcuMRZ9mUMb1tLiucj98a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"AH HA! I found it! Look at the test `before_each()`:\n\n```gdscript\n_container = Node3D.new()\n_manager = TravelSequenceManager.new()\n_manager.setup(null, null, _container)\n```\n\nThe `_manager` is created but **never added to the tree** (`add_child` is never called). And `_container` is also never added to the tree.\n\nNow look at `setup()`:\n```gdscript\nfunc setup(player: Node3D, ship_exterior: ShipExterior, biome_container: Node3D) -> void:\n\n\n```\n\nIt stores the references, connects to the navigation signal, and then calls `_build_fade_overlay()`. But that function checks `is_inside_tree()` first—and since the manager was never added to the scene tree, it returns early without initializing `_fade_rect` or `_fade_layer`, leaving them as null.\n\nSo when the travel completes and `_fade_out()` gets called, it returns early because there's no fade rect. The coroutine still completes though, so `execute_biome_swap()` runs anyway, then `_fade_in()` also returns early. The whole sequence works in the test because the fade functions gracefully skip their work when the UI elements don't exist.\n\nBut that raises the question—if the fade functions are returning early in the test, what's actually happening in the real game when everything is properly initialized?\n\n```\nIn the real game, `_fade_out()` creates a tween and awaits `tween.finished` for 0.5 seconds. The\n```\n\nIn the actual game, the fade functions would create tweens and wait for them to complete, which takes real time. The biome swap would only happen after that fade-out finishes.\n\nLet me trace through how Godot handles this: when `_on_travel_completed` is a coroutine connected to a signal, it starts running synchronously, but when it hits an `await`, it suspends and control returns to whoever emitted the signal. Once the awaited condition is met, the coroutine resumes from where it left off.\n\nSo after `travel_completed.emit()` fires the coroutine, the `initiate_travel` function continues and emits `biome_changed`, which synchronously runs the respawn system's handler. Then `initiate_travel` returns and we're back in the event loop. Meanwhile, the suspended coroutine is waiting on the tween to finish—once the tween completes after 0.5 seconds, the coroutine resumes and continues through the rest of the sequence.\n\nThe tween should process fine since `set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(false)` only sets a flag and doesn't pause the tree. But let me look at what TestWorld's `_process` method is actually doing...\n\nIt runs every frame and checks if `_transitioning` is true before updating interactions, but that flag shouldn't affect tween processing either. So the tweens should be running. The real question is whether the fade and biome swap are actually happening, or if something's getting stuck—maybe the fade-in is hanging and leaving the player in a black screen state.\n\nBut the producer was clear: no fade appears at all, no scene change, nothing. The player just gets locked in place. That suggests `_on_travel_completed` might never be firing in the first place, which would explain why input stays disabled and nothing visual happens. If that signal isn't connecting or firing, the entire transition chain breaks. So I need to figure out why that handler isn't being called—either the signal connection is missing, or something's preventing it from firing.\n\nLooking at the disconnect logic, `teardown()` explicitly removes the signal connection, but I need to find where that's actually being called to see if it's happening at the wrong time.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8341,"cache_read_input_tokens":96687,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8341},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"0a52373a-eaf6-4d4e-ad52-0f9495def8db"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GGcuMRZ9mUMb1tLiucj98a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PGSogtaEvwLxFDQyCRE6A9","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"teardown\\(\\)","path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\levels\\test_world.gd","output_mode":"content","-n":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8341,"cache_read_input_tokens":96687,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8341},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c