ure"},{"content":"Verify all acceptance criteria met","status":"pending","activeForm":"Verifying acceptance criteria"},{"content":"Commit, push, create PR, and update ticket","status":"pending","activeForm":"Committing and pushing changes"}]}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BvJ3oSCH5EeKSd48TyWqPq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"After thorough analysis, I've identified the root cause. The `_on_travel_completed` signal handler is a coroutine (contains `await`) that gets invoked synchronously during the `travel_completed.emit()` call stack chain. When the coroutine suspends at `await _fade_out()`, the tween's `finished` signal cannot properly resume the coroutine because it was created within the nested signal emission context. The fix is to separate the signal handler (synchronous) from the async transition worker, ensuring the coroutine runs in a clean context.\n\nLet me implement the fix:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14946,"cache_read_input_tokens":118803,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14946},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"51c7b155-5a26-4089-b6f5-bb88a2ca1f43"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BvJ3oSCH5EeKSd48TyWqPq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H1B8y7fpK4Jz4P995Fc1bp","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\.claude\\worktrees\\orch-gameplay-programmer-TICKET-0247\\game\\scripts\\gameplay\\travel_sequence_manager.gd","old_string":"## Handles NavigationSystem.travel_completed — runs the full async travel\n## transition: disable input, fade out, swap biome, fade in, re-enable input.\nfunc _on_travel_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\tif _is_transitioning:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: ignoring travel_completed — already transitioning\")\n\t\treturn\n\n\t_is_transitioning = true\n\ttravel_sequence_started.emit(destination_id)\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(false)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\t# Fade to black\n\tawait _fade_out()\n\n\t# Swap biome content\n\tvar success: bool = execute_biome_swap(destination_id)\n\n\tif not success:\n\t\t# Error recovery: fade back in and restore input\n\t\tpush_error(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap failed for '%s' — recovering\" % destination_id)\n\t\tawait _fade_in()\n\t\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t\t_is_transitioning = false\n\t\treturn\n\n\t# Fade back in\n\tawait _fade_in()\n\n\t# Restore input and mark transition complete\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t_is_transitioning = false\n\ttravel_sequence_completed.emit(destination_id)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)","new_string":"## Handles NavigationSystem.travel_completed — guards against double-entry,\n## then delegates the async transition to _execute_travel_transition.\n## This handler is intentionally NOT a coroutine: the signal fires\n## synchronously inside NavigationSystem.initiate_travel(), and a coroutine\n## that suspends mid-signal-emission can prevent the tween's finished signal\n## from resuming it. Separating the sync handler from the async worker\n## ensures the await chain runs in a clean call context.\nfunc _on_travel_completed(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\tif _is_transitioning:\n\t\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: ignoring travel_completed — already transitioning\")\n\t\treturn\n\n\t_is_transitioning = true\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel_completed received for '%s' — starting transition\" % destination_id)\n\t_execute_travel_transition(destination_id)\n\n\n## Runs the full async travel transition: disable input, fade out, swap biome,\n## fade in, re-enable input. Called from _on_travel_completed in a clean context.\nfunc _execute_travel_transition(destination_id: String) -> void:\n\ttravel_sequence_started.emit(destination_id)\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(false)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence started → '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\t# Fade to black\n\tawait _fade_out()\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: fade-out complete for '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\t# Swap biome content\n\tvar success: bool = execute_biome_swap(destination_id)\n\n\tif not success:\n\t\t# Error recovery: fade back in and restore input\n\t\tpush_error(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap failed for '%s' — recovering\" % destination_id)\n\t\tawait _fade_in()\n\t\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t\t_is_transitioning = false\n\t\treturn\n\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: biome swap succeeded for '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\t# Fade back in\n\tawait _fade_in()\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: fade-in complete for '%s'\" % destination_id)\n\n\t# Restore input and mark transition complete\n\tInputManager.set_gameplay_inputs_enabled(true)\n\t_is_transitioning = false\n\ttravel_sequence_completed.emit(destination_id)\n\tGlobal.log(\"TravelSequenceManager: travel sequence completed → '%s'\" % destination_id)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14946,"cache_read_input_tokens":118803,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14946},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e95448fc-7558-4157-960a-6c7229146ac9","uuid":"bdb88c75-fada-48ac-a59d-144794e24100"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","cont