,"status":"completed","activeForm":"Investigating travel sequence code"},{"content":"Identify and fix root cause of biome transition not triggering","status":"completed","activeForm":"Fixing root cause of biome transition failure"},{"content":"Verify all acceptance criteria met","status":"completed","activeForm":"Verifying acceptance criteria"},{"content":"Commit, push, create PR, and update ticket","status":"completed","activeForm":"Committing and pushing changes"}]}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Uw4KsSE4SVrX7xWwQXQqsF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"ticket\": \"TICKET-0247\", \"outcome\": \"done\", \"summary\": \"Fixed biome transition not triggering after CONFIRM TRAVEL. Root cause: _on_travel_completed was a coroutine (contained await) connected as a signal handler to NavigationSystem.travel_completed. When the signal fires synchronously inside initiate_travel(), the coroutine suspends at await _fade_out() within the signal emission call stack, and the tween's finished signal cannot properly resume it. Fix: split _on_travel_completed into a synchronous signal handler (sets _is_transitioning guard) and a separate _execute_travel_transition coroutine that runs the async fade/swap/fade sequence in a clean call context. Added comprehensive logging at every transition phase. Ticket left as IN_PROGRESS with READY FOR STUDIO HEAD SIGN-OFF per hold condition.\", \"commit_hash\": \"b16df22\", \"pr_url\": \"https://github.com/sqlhammer/Hammer-Forge-Studio/pull/213\", \"files_changed\": [\"game/scripts/gameplay/travel_sequence_manager.gd\", \"game/scripts/systems/navigation_system.gd\", \"tickets/M8/TICKET-0247.md\"], \"new_gd_scripts\": false, \"blockers\": []}"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":315,"cache_read_input_tokens":159397,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":315},"output_tokens":1